        "description": {
            "value": "<p>You arrange a spiky cage of bones, particularly tough vegetation, or other material to spring up when disturbed. The snare deals [[/r 9d8 #piercing]] piercing damage to the first creature to enter this square; that creature must attempt a DC 31 Reflex save.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature is knocked aside by the snareâ€™s deployment, taking half damage, and is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.AJh5ex99aV6VTggg]{Flat-Footed} until the end of its next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature is captured by the cage, taking full damage and falling @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.j91X7x0XSomq8d60]{Prone}. It is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.eIcWbB5o3pP6OIMe]{Immobilized} while it remains within the cage. It can get free by @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.SkZAQRkLLkmBQNB9]{Escaping} (DC 31) or by destroying the cage (Hardness 5, HP 30, object immunities).</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but the creature takes double damage.</p>",
